    "title": "Career Opportunity Medical Officer at Wockhardt Hospitals",
    "description": "Wockhardt Hospitals has an exciting opening for a Medical Officer at our Mysuru office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Wockhardt Hospitals:\nWockhardt Hospitals is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Maintain accurate clinical documentation in electronic health records\n• Conduct routine health assessments and screenings\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Sc / M.Sc in Life Sciences\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in HIPAA Compliance\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n• Proficiency in ICU Management\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Mysuru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Wockhardt Hospitals!",
